5
00:01:40,567 --> 00:01:44,404
Recently, we've shown many shortcomings during rescue operations,

6
00:01:44,404 --> 00:01:46,439
especially in terms of medical assistance.

7
00:01:47,441 --> 00:01:50,702
How do you all feel about it? Let's talk about this.

8
00:01:50,702 --> 00:01:51,866
Instructor.

9
00:01:52,698 --> 00:01:54,014
Here's the thing.

10
00:01:54,014 --> 00:01:57,216
Simple first aid and bandaging, we can handle that without any issues, right?

11
00:01:57,216 --> 00:01:58,001
Yes.

12
00:01:58,001 --> 00:02:00,988
But when it comes to more complex injuries, we don't have the skills for it.

13
00:02:00,988 --> 00:02:05,459
Besides, treating injuries isn't our primary duty as firefighters.

14
00:02:05,459 --> 00:02:07,427
The main thing is we're not very knowledgeable in that area.

15
00:02:07,427 --> 00:02:09,601
- Instructor, Captain, I have an idea. 
 - Go on.

16
00:02:09,601 --> 00:02:12,265
Can't we coordinate with medical units

17
00:02:12,265 --> 00:02:14,835
so that when the fire truck arrives, an ambulance can also be dispatched?

18
00:02:14,835 --> 00:02:16,572
Having professional doctors and nurses present

19
00:02:16,572 --> 00:02:18,939
would ensure the injured receive immediate assistance.

20
00:02:18,939 --> 00:02:23,632
Instructor, Dapeng's idea is something we have considered before.

21
00:02:23,632 --> 00:02:25,578
For example, when we encounter injured individuals at the scene,

22
00:02:25,578 --> 00:02:27,948
we can call for an ambulance. That's not a problem.

23
00:02:27,948 --> 00:02:30,917
But having a medical vehicle on standby with us every day during missions,

24
00:02:30,917 --> 00:02:32,138
that's not very realistic.

25
00:02:32,138 --> 00:02:34,005
After all, we're of different systems.

26
00:02:34,005 --> 00:02:35,989
Isn't that the same as saying nothing at all?

27
00:02:35,989 --> 00:02:37,670
You are both right.

28
00:02:38,280 --> 00:02:40,039
What do you think?

29
00:02:41,261 --> 00:02:44,197
Rescue scenes are filled with complexities.

30
00:02:44,197 --> 00:02:46,967
Finding solutions is not difficult,

31
00:02:46,967 --> 00:02:48,820
but implementing them is challenging.

32
00:02:50,665 --> 00:02:52,846
Nothing worth having comes easy.

33
00:02:54,065 --> 00:02:55,847
I want to give it a try.

34
00:03:00,319 --> 00:03:01,999
- Training time! 
 - Let's go.

35
00:03:01,999 --> 00:03:03,900
Let's go.

36
00:03:03,900 --> 00:03:06,600
- Oh, it's too hot. 
 - Yes.

37
00:03:11,472 --> 00:03:13,835
   

38
00:03:13,835 --> 00:03:17,735
Establishing a Fire and Paramedic Joint Rescue Team,

39
00:03:18,860 --> 00:03:23,438
is it a sudden inspiration or a long-standing contemplation?

40
00:03:23,438 --> 00:03:26,674
Commissar, in the previous fire incident in the old neigborhood,

41
00:03:26,674 --> 00:03:31,678
we received a call stating that it was an uninhabited area slated for demolition.

42
00:03:31,678 --> 00:03:36,149
However, upon arriving at the scene, we discovered a child who was severely injured.

43
00:03:36,149 --> 00:03:40,480
We carried out emergency treatment and took her to the hospital.

44
00:03:40,480 --> 00:03:42,325
Also, a few days ago,

45
00:03:42,325 --> 00:03:45,092
we found a seriously injured hiker deep in the mountains.

46
00:03:45,092 --> 00:03:49,140
We sought assistance from a doctor via satellite phone.

47
00:03:49,140 --> 00:03:51,460
These two incidents made me deeply reflect.

48
00:03:51,460 --> 00:03:54,442
If we had a paramedic on hand,

49
00:03:54,442 --> 00:03:58,373
we could have responded more quickly and efficiently,

50
00:03:58,373 --> 00:04:01,040
significantly reducing the casualty rate.

51
00:04:01,040 --> 00:04:05,593
This has been my recent contemplation and a long-held idea.

52
00:04:06,747 --> 00:04:10,783
It'd indeed be ideal if doctors could be present at the scene for immediate treatment.

53
00:04:12,252 --> 00:04:16,759
However, our medical and fire departments currently operate under different organizations,

54
00:04:16,759 --> 00:04:19,827
so there may be some coordination delays.

55
00:04:19,827 --> 00:04:22,700
But it's still within our control.

56
00:04:22,700 --> 00:04:26,500
It would be beneficial if we could provide rescue training for doctors

57
00:04:26,500 --> 00:04:31,659
and enhance the collaboration between the two departments.

58
00:04:33,207 --> 00:04:35,978
While your suggestion is good,

59
00:04:35,978 --> 00:04:40,414
having doctors and firefighters enter the first scene together

60
00:04:40,414 --> 00:04:42,112
is not something to be taken lightly.

61
00:04:42,112 --> 00:04:48,121
Have you thought about how to improve their response capabilities

62
00:04:48,121 --> 00:04:49,505
while ensuring their safety?

63
00:04:49,505 --> 00:04:52,979
Have firefighters provide targeted training for medical personnel

64
00:04:52,979 --> 00:04:55,979
and establish safety protocols.

65
00:04:57,030 --> 00:05:01,401
Looks like you already have some ideas about the training aspect.

66
00:05:01,401 --> 00:05:02,801
By the way...

67
00:05:04,671 --> 00:05:07,310
Commissar, I have a proposal here.

68
00:05:16,750 --> 00:05:19,251
You've come well-prepared.

69
00:05:20,057 --> 00:05:23,097
You've always wanted to work at the grassroots level.

70
00:05:23,097 --> 00:05:25,826
I was worried you might have some difficulty adjusting.

71
00:05:25,826 --> 00:05:27,945
How is it working with Song Yan?

72
00:05:27,945 --> 00:05:31,602
He has been of great help to me and has shown great support.

73
00:05:33,085 --> 00:05:35,002
I know his temper well.

74
00:05:35,002 --> 00:05:38,242
It's not easy for you two to work together.

75
00:05:40,107 --> 00:05:41,709
All right.

76
00:05:41,709 --> 00:05:45,260
I will submit your proposal to the higher authorities.

77
00:05:45,260 --> 00:05:49,883
Let's strive to make Shili Tai a pilot unit and collaborate with the city hospital.

78
00:05:49,883 --> 00:05:51,483
Thank you, Commissar.

79
00:05:53,497 --> 00:05:55,388
Thank you for taking the trip here.

80
00:05:55,388 --> 00:05:58,310
I wish for a successful collaboration between our units.

81
00:05:58,310 --> 00:06:01,791
Also, please consider the media coverage aspect.

82
00:06:01,791 --> 00:06:03,671
After all, it's a form of publicity.

83
00:06:03,671 --> 00:06:05,832
Thank you, Assistant Director Liu. You donâ€™t need to walk us out.

84
00:06:05,832 --> 00:06:07,637
See you next time.

85
00:06:12,209 --> 00:06:14,174
He only wants the superficial stuff.

86
00:06:14,174 --> 00:06:16,543
As long as we can get real work done, it doesn't matter.

87
00:06:16,543 --> 00:06:18,550
What real work?

88
00:06:18,550 --> 00:06:21,671
I've always disagreed with the establishment of a joint rescue team.

89
00:06:21,671 --> 00:06:23,216
And I still hold that stance.

90
00:06:23,216 --> 00:06:25,585
Doctors and nurses have insufficient knowledge of fire scenes

91
00:06:25,585 --> 00:06:27,351
and can't carry out practical operations.

92
00:06:27,351 --> 00:06:30,031
I didn't say they have to enter the fire scene.

93
00:06:30,031 --> 00:06:33,950
I'll train them properly and prioritize safety, all right?

94
00:06:33,950 --> 00:06:35,557
You're oversimplifying things.

95
00:06:35,557 --> 00:06:39,550
Are the doctors and nurses part of the hospital or the fire station?

96
00:06:39,550 --> 00:06:41,890
When their work at the hospital conflicts with firefighting,

97
00:06:41,890 --> 00:06:44,011
which side will they prioritize?

98
00:06:44,011 --> 00:06:47,617
That's why I say you're just full of impractical ideas.

99
00:06:47,617 --> 00:06:49,476
These aren't impractical ideas.

100
00:06:49,476 --> 00:06:50,704
We'll start with a pilot project.

101
00:06:50,704 --> 00:06:52,312
Wouldn't it be great to have

102
00:06:52,312 --> 00:06:54,681
professional medical personnel cooperating with firefighters?

103
00:06:54,681 --> 00:06:56,791
- We're getting off track. 
 - Let's bring it back then.

104
00:06:56,791 --> 00:07:00,190
Once the joint rescue team is established, you will need to do the training...

105
00:07:00,190 --> 00:07:01,790
I'm sorry.

106
00:07:04,330 --> 00:07:06,130
What a coincidence.

107
00:07:08,179 --> 00:07:10,290
What are you doing here?

108
00:07:10,290 --> 00:07:13,631
We're here to talk about the joint rescue team.

109
00:07:13,631 --> 00:07:16,811
Allow me to introduce. This is Song Yan, our captain.

110
00:07:21,791 --> 00:07:23,371
You know each other?

111
00:07:23,371 --> 00:07:25,171
- No. 
 - Yes.

112
00:07:26,650 --> 00:07:28,550
- Sort of. 
 - No.

113
00:07:31,585 --> 00:07:34,110
You guys go ahead. I'll leave now.

114
00:07:38,274 --> 00:07:40,101
What's with you two?

115
00:07:41,770 --> 00:07:43,707
None of your business.

116
00:07:45,870 --> 00:07:50,251
Aren't you going to ask how I met her?

117
00:07:50,251 --> 00:07:52,069
None of my business.

118
00:07:52,706 --> 00:07:54,731
- All right. 
 - Please.

119
00:07:54,731 --> 00:07:57,731
It'll take five business days for the report to come out.

120
00:07:57,731 --> 00:08:00,611
- Thank you. 
 - It's my job. Goodbye, President Meng.

121
00:08:07,048 --> 00:08:09,862
   

122
00:08:31,631 --> 00:08:33,131
Brother.

123
00:08:34,337 --> 00:08:35,716
Did you finish your check-up?

124
00:08:35,716 --> 00:08:37,331
What do you want to eat for lunch?

125
00:08:37,331 --> 00:08:39,231
Why haven't you get changed?

126
00:08:39,231 --> 00:08:42,131
I was thinking we could just eat at the cafeteria.

127
00:08:42,131 --> 00:08:44,530
I thought I could take you out for a nice lunch.

128
00:08:44,530 --> 00:08:47,650
Bro, I'm really busy, okay?

129
00:08:50,169 --> 00:08:52,256
Do you think our cafeteria is not good enough?

130
00:08:52,256 --> 00:08:55,402
No. I don't mind trying it.

131
00:08:55,402 --> 00:08:58,177
Do you remember when we were little and you couldn't get enough to eat,

132
00:08:58,177 --> 00:09:00,674
and I'd sneak you out to grab something?

133
00:09:00,674 --> 00:09:02,670
I don't remember.

134
00:09:02,670 --> 00:09:04,441
Do you really not remember?

135
00:09:09,091 --> 00:09:11,351
You have to support it.

136
00:09:12,119 --> 00:09:14,242
We run into each other again.

137
00:09:15,789 --> 00:09:17,836
What brings you to the hospital?

138
00:09:21,261 --> 00:09:22,591
Medical check-up.

139
00:09:22,591 --> 00:09:25,190
- And you? 
 - Work.

140
00:09:25,190 --> 00:09:27,231
Allow me to introduce.

141
00:09:27,231 --> 00:09:29,750
This is Song Yan, the captain of our fire station.

142
00:09:29,750 --> 00:09:32,991
This is Meng Yan Chen. Xu Qin's brother.

143
00:09:37,990 --> 00:09:39,150
You know each other?

144
00:09:39,150 --> 00:09:40,850
- No. 
 - No.

145
00:09:41,831 --> 00:09:43,710
Say hi to each other then.

146
00:09:48,471 --> 00:09:49,971
Hi.

147
00:09:52,030 --> 00:09:53,730
Hi.

148
00:09:57,431 --> 00:09:58,910
Let's go, Brother.

149
00:09:58,910 --> 00:10:00,840
We should get going.

150
00:10:25,650 --> 00:10:27,890
Assistant Director Liu.

151
00:10:27,890 --> 00:10:32,371
Madam Fu, Song Yan is now the captain of a fire station.

152
00:10:36,050 --> 00:10:38,170
I don't know him.

153
00:10:41,650 --> 00:10:44,170
Yes. You don't know him.

154
00:10:44,170 --> 00:10:46,551
I misspoke. It's nothing.

155
00:11:15,950 --> 00:11:19,500
   

156
00:11:23,050 --> 00:11:26,810
Take your time. Read it well.

157
00:11:26,810 --> 00:11:29,650
This concerns the hospital's reputation.

158
00:11:30,510 --> 00:11:33,906
It's also an opportunity for your emergency department to showcase their abilities.

159
00:11:38,131 --> 00:11:40,770
I know you don't care,

160
00:11:40,770 --> 00:11:44,691
but it's also a good opportunity for the young people in your department.

161
00:11:49,176 --> 00:11:51,689
If you have any suggestions, feel free to speak up.

162
00:11:53,371 --> 00:11:58,471
I think it's inappropriate for doctors to stay at the fire station for training.

163
00:11:58,471 --> 00:12:00,754
Moreover, they are required to go to the frontline.

164
00:12:00,754 --> 00:12:03,431
The situation at the frontline is filled with uncertainties.

165
00:12:03,431 --> 00:12:05,890
Who will guarantee the safety of the doctors?

166
00:12:10,611 --> 00:12:13,800
You just hit the nail on the head with these two points.

167
00:12:13,800 --> 00:12:16,336
How can we ensure the safety of doctors at the frontline?

168
00:12:16,336 --> 00:12:18,404
Don't they need appropriate knowledge to deal with such situations?

169
00:12:18,404 --> 00:12:19,904
And where does this knowledge come from?

170
00:12:19,904 --> 00:12:22,242
Isn't it derived from regular training?

171
00:12:22,242 --> 00:12:25,235
If you don't train well, how can you treat and save lives?

172
00:12:27,679 --> 00:12:29,650
You shouldn't be concerned about that right now.

173
00:12:29,650 --> 00:12:32,410
You should just about who should be chosen for this task.

174
00:12:32,410 --> 00:12:34,183
No need to think about it.

175
00:12:35,831 --> 00:12:37,531
Send me.

176
00:12:38,770 --> 00:12:40,393
I'm not joking.

177
00:12:40,393 --> 00:12:42,424
I'm telling you this is a task assigned by Director Wang.

178
00:12:42,424 --> 00:12:45,263
If you have a problem with it, take it up with him.

179
00:12:58,720 --> 00:13:02,290
   

180
00:13:02,290 --> 00:13:04,000
   

181
00:13:06,570 --> 00:13:09,210
Department Chief, I want to go.

182
00:13:10,410 --> 00:13:12,510
What's your reason?

183
00:13:12,510 --> 00:13:14,410
Someone in our department has to go anyway.

184
00:13:14,410 --> 00:13:17,864
Whether it's at the hospital or at the frontline, it's all about saving lives.

185
00:13:17,864 --> 00:13:19,530
The responsibilities of doctors haven't changed.

186
00:13:19,530 --> 00:13:21,629
Do you really think so?

187
00:13:23,351 --> 00:13:26,431
All right. I got it.

188
00:13:28,410 --> 00:13:30,990
Then, I shall get back to work.

189
00:13:30,990 --> 00:13:32,390
Okay.

190
00:13:47,491 --> 00:13:49,791
- Li Nan. 
 - Team Leader.

191
00:13:50,930 --> 00:13:53,971
I thought you didn't want to join the rescue team.

192
00:13:53,971 --> 00:13:55,383
I'm sorry.

193
00:13:55,383 --> 00:13:58,649
I made a decision on my own without consulting you.

194
00:13:58,649 --> 00:14:03,036
It's okay. The higher up has decidedto send our group anyway.

195
00:14:03,810 --> 00:14:06,451
Okay. I'll let you pack up. I'm leaving.

196
00:14:06,451 --> 00:14:08,351
- Bye-bye. 
 - Bye-bye.

197
00:14:21,011 --> 00:14:23,970
What's the purpose of your visit today?

198
00:14:24,597 --> 00:14:26,451
I came to say goodbye.

199
00:14:26,451 --> 00:14:29,030
I'm leaving in a couple days.

200
00:14:29,030 --> 00:14:31,750
I'm planning to go on a six-month trip first.

201
00:14:31,750 --> 00:14:34,191
If I enjoy it, I'll visit West Africa too.

202
00:14:34,191 --> 00:14:36,204
You're leaving, huh?

203
00:14:37,231 --> 00:14:38,870
You really live in the moment.

204
00:14:38,870 --> 00:14:42,051
This is what I call enjoying life.

205
00:14:44,591 --> 00:14:46,270
I envy you sometimes.

206
00:14:46,270 --> 00:14:48,231
You can do it too, you know.

207
00:14:53,170 --> 00:14:56,131
How are things going between you and him?

208
00:14:56,131 --> 00:14:59,271
In the past, I didn't want to hurt him,

209
00:15:00,066 --> 00:15:02,535
but now I keep hesitating.

210
00:15:02,535 --> 00:15:05,476
It's not only hurting him, but also hurting myself.

211
00:15:06,540 --> 00:15:11,340
I used to believe that as long as I was willing, he wouldn't leave, but now...

212
00:15:11,340 --> 00:15:14,018
Well, you brought it upon yourself.

213
00:15:15,449 --> 00:15:17,383
Perhaps.

214
00:15:17,383 --> 00:15:22,437
Maybe, instinctively, I want to test his limits repeatedly.

215
00:15:24,789 --> 00:15:28,323
Or maybe it's as he said,

216
00:15:28,323 --> 00:15:33,030
you're only considering going back to him because you haven't found someone new to like.

217
00:15:33,810 --> 00:15:35,535
I don't know either.

218
00:15:35,535 --> 00:15:40,206
Sometimes I wonder if I've lost the ability to love,

219
00:15:40,206 --> 00:15:42,975
that's why I keep getting stuck in the past.

220
00:15:42,975 --> 00:15:44,912
But no matter how much I say it,

221
00:15:44,912 --> 00:15:46,996
when it really comes down to it,

222
00:15:48,111 --> 00:15:49,782
I still don't want to give up.

223
00:15:49,782 --> 00:15:52,589
That's Song Yan we're talking about. Who wants to give up on him?

224
00:15:52,589 --> 00:15:55,109
So, what's your plan?

225
00:15:55,109 --> 00:15:58,591
If he takes a step towards me, I'll take a step towards him.

226
00:15:58,591 --> 00:16:00,390
Just like he said,

227
00:16:00,390 --> 00:16:02,295
he doesn't know the present me

228
00:16:02,295 --> 00:16:06,211
and doesn't know if the present me is worth his liking.

229
00:16:06,211 --> 00:16:09,491
And as for me, I also don't know the present him.

230
00:16:09,491 --> 00:16:13,807
I don't know if the present him is the one I truly like.

231
00:16:13,807 --> 00:16:15,407
So...

232
00:16:16,477 --> 00:16:18,569
We're getting to know each other again.

233
00:16:20,200 --> 00:16:23,770
   

234
00:16:50,075 --> 00:16:53,111
They are doctors and nurses from the city hospital.

235
00:16:53,111 --> 00:16:58,658
They are here in our Shili Tai Fire Station to form a joint rescue team with us.

236
00:16:58,658 --> 00:17:01,139
Let's give them a round of applause.

237
00:17:05,057 --> 00:17:06,870
Let me introduce myself.

238
00:17:06,870 --> 00:17:09,171
My name is Jiang Yu. I'm the instructor.

239
00:17:09,171 --> 00:17:12,411
This is Song Yan, Captain Song.

240
00:17:12,411 --> 00:17:13,911
Hi.

241
00:17:15,675 --> 00:17:18,983
Let's introduce ourselves to each other and get to know each other.

242
00:17:19,691 --> 00:17:23,551
I'm Xu Xi, a nurse from the emergency department.

243
00:17:23,551 --> 00:17:26,511
Please take care of me.

244
00:17:26,511 --> 00:17:29,931
I'm Chen Dongdong, a nurse from the emergency department.

245
00:17:31,111 --> 00:17:34,430
I'm Xu Qin, a doctor from the emergency department.

246
00:17:37,591 --> 00:17:40,591
I'm Li Nan, a doctor from the emergency department.

247
00:17:42,150 --> 00:17:45,130
I'm Feng Bei, a nurse from the emergency department.

248
00:17:46,470 --> 00:17:51,491
Let's once again welcome Dr. Xu Qin and her medical team.

249
00:18:01,430 --> 00:18:03,691
Hi, Captain Song. 
    

250
00:18:06,810 --> 00:18:09,230
Hi, Dr. Xu.

251
00:18:11,150 --> 00:18:12,470
This way, please.

252
00:18:12,470 --> 00:18:13,831
Welcome, everyone.

253
00:18:13,831 --> 00:18:16,397
- Give them a warm welcome. 
  - Warmer, warmer.

254
00:18:19,150 --> 00:18:21,311
- Warmer, warmer. 
 - Please come in.

255
00:18:21,311 --> 00:18:22,751
Welcome!

256
00:18:22,751 --> 00:18:24,111
Here is our dormitory.

257
00:18:24,111 --> 00:18:26,190
Feel free to take a look around.

258
00:18:26,190 --> 00:18:30,290
You boys' dormitory is so tidy.

